issue.title: Fix pings
issue.body:
- [x] Upgraded some really outdated dependencies.
- [x] Fixed pings to work with the latest websocket proxy protocol.
- [x] Fixed some rooms not giving verbal directions. (They weren't being lower-cased against the directions object list.)

issue.title: Esnext ify
issue.body:
Everything refactored into ES6, and broken up into modules. Could probably use some more refactoring later, but I think this is a good first pass.

![](https://media.giphy.com/media/lhuyyupeH9cJ2/giphy.gif)

Tested that is works, and it's actually running the new bundled code on the office Echo right now.

issue.title: Soi 55
issue.body:
Converted code to ES6, implemented Webpack bundling so that we can we use modules.

@dagarfin Please give this a test. Running `npm start` generates `/dist/bundle.js` which should be able to be used in place of the old `officeInsightIndex.js`. Note that `config.json` (which is gitignored) needs to be created locally, but you can leave it an empty `{}`.
